{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 14,
  "title": "第十四章（道紀）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "視之而弗見，名之曰「微」。"
    },
    {
      "text": "聽之而弗聞，名之曰「希」。"
    },
    {
      "text": "捪之而弗得，名之曰「夷」。"
    },
    {
      "text": "三者不可至計，故混而為一。"
    },
    {
      "text": "「一」者："
    },
    {
      "text": "亓上不攸，亓下不忽。"
    },
    {
      "text": "尋尋呵，不可名也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "復歸於无物。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是謂无狀之狀。"
    },
    {
      "text": "无物之象，是謂惚恍。"
    },
    {
      "text": "隨而不見亓後，"
    },
    {
      "text": "迎而不見亓首。"
    },
    {
      "text": "執今之道，以御今之有。"
    },
    {
      "text": "以知古始，是謂道紀。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無色曰夷。言一無采色，不可得視而見之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無聲曰希。言一無音聲，不可得聽而聞之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無形曰微。言一無形體，不可摶持而得之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "三者，謂夷、希、微也。不可致詰者，夫無色、無聲、無形，口不能言，書不能傳，當受之以靜，求之以神，不可問詰而得之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 49,
          "end": 50
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "混，合也。故合於三名之為一。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言一在天上，不皦。皦，光明。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言一在天下，不昧。昧，有所闇冥。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "繩繩者，動行無窮級也。不可名者，非一色也，不可以青黃白黑別，非一聲也，不可以宮商角徵羽聽，非一形也，不可以長短大小度之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 27,
          "end": 28
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "物，質也。復當歸之於無質。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言一無形狀，而能為萬物作形狀也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一無物質，而為萬物設形象也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言一忽忽恍恍者，若存若亡，不可見之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一無端末，不可預待也。除情去欲，一自歸之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言一無影跡，不可得而看。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人執守古道，生一以御物，知今當有一也。能知古始，是謂道紀。人能知上古本始有一，是謂知道綱紀也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無狀無象，無聲無響，故能無所不通，無所不往，不得而知，更以我耳目體不知為名，故不可致詰，混而為一也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "欲言無邪，而物由以成。欲言有邪，而不見其形，故曰，無狀之狀，無物之象也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 13,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不可得而定也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有，有其事。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無形無名者，萬物之宗也。雖今古不同，時移俗易，故莫不由乎此以成其治者也。故可執古之道，以御今之有。上古雖遠，其道存焉，故雖在今，可以知古始也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
